<body>
  <div id="main" class="active">
    <div class="container">
      <section class="container" id="Q1">
      	<h1>Code Challenge</h1>
        <p class="small note demoNote">
          Note: Open console to see more precise calculated time. Press "Enter" while in an input box or click a buttons to start a event
        </p>
        <p>1. Given two rectangles, check if they overlap. Please define and explain your rectangle definition</p>
        <svg>
          <rect id="rectangle1"/>
          <rect id="rectangle2"/>
        </svg>
        <form>
          Rectangle 1
          <div class="center" id="rect1input">
            <div>
              <div id="x1">
                <input type="text" placeholder="x">
                <span class="validation"></span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div id="y1">
                <input type="text" placeholder="y">
                <span class="validation"></span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div id="width1">
                <input type="text" placeholder="Width">
                <span class="validation"></span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div id="height1">
                <input type="text" placeholder="Height">
                <span class="validation"></span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          Rectangle 2
          <div class="center" id="rect2input">
            <div>
              <div id="x2">
                <input type="text" placeholder="x">
                <span class="validation"></span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div id="y2">
                <input type="text" placeholder="y">
                <span class="validation"></span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div id="width2">
                <input type="text" placeholder="Width">
                <span class="validation"></span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div id="height2">
                <input type="text" placeholder="Height">
                <span class="validation"></span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="centerText">
            <span id="overlap"></span><br>
            Time: <span id="overlapTime">0</span>ms<br>
            <a class="button" id="overlapBtn" href="javascript:overlapFunction();">Check Overlap</a>
          </p>
        </form>
      </section>
      <section class="container" id="Q2">
        <p>2. Given an array: [a_1, a_2, ..., a_N, b_1, b_2, ..., b_N, c_1, c_2, ..., c_N]<br>
            efficiently convert it to: [a_1, b_1, c_1, a_2, b_2, c_2, ..., a_N, b_N, c_N]<br>
            Please try to use as little space as possible.
        </p>
        <h2 id="Q2array">
          []
        </h2>
        <h2 id="Q2newArray">
          []
        </h2>
        <form>
          <div class="center">
            <input type="text" placeholder="# of letters" id="nA">
            <input type="text" placeholder="N" id="N">
          </div>
          <p class="centerText">
            Time: <span id="reorderTime">0</span>ms<br>
            <a class="button" href="javascript:arrayFunction();">Reorder Array</a>
          </p>
        </form>
      </section>
      <section class="container" id="Q2">
        <p>3. Given a set of words, find the longest word which is the concatenation of other words in the set. For example, if the set is { "hell", "hello", "foo", "hellobarfoo", "world", "foobar", "bar" }, the word weâ€™re looking for is "hellobarfoo".
        </p>
        <h2 id="Q3array">
          [hell, hello, foo, hellobarfoo, world, foobar, bar]
        </h2>
        <h2 id="concatenation">
          []
        </h2>
        <form>
          Enter new array, seperated by comma ","<br>
            hell, hello, foo, hellobarfoo, world, foobar, bar
          <div class="center">
            <input type="text" placeholder="Words array" id="newArray"></input>
          </div>
          <p class="centerText">
            Time: <span id="concatenationTime">0</span>ms<br>
            <a class="button" href="javascript:concatenationFunction();">Concatenation</a>
          </p>
        </form>
      </section>
